added.title: The Bergerac
added.description: The Titans give Robin advice to guide him through his camp romance with Wonder Girl.

added.title: Butt Atoms
added.description: Despite Robin's warning, the Titans mess around with atomic toots and end up causing a worldwide plague.

added.title: Witches Brew
added.description: The Titans throw a Halloween party and invite the Justice League but the witches brew Robin creates has side effects.

added.title: Rocknaldo
added.description: Ronaldo sets out to find all the rock people living in Beach City!

added.title: Restaurant Wars
added.description: Steven must help the Frymans and the Pizzas settle a reignited rivalry between their restaurants.

added.title: Reformed
added.description: Steven, Amethyst and Garnet chase after a monster that's been loose in the Temple.

added.title: Onion Friend
added.description: Steven and Amethyst visit the strange world of Onion's house.

added.title: Joking Victim
added.description: When Lars pawns off all his work on Sadie, Steven helps out by working a shift at the Big Donut.

added.title: Meet Lion-O
added.description: Meet Lion-O and the Thundercats! After fleeing their home planet, the Thundercats find themselves stranded on Third Earth where they face the evil Mumm-Ra. But Lion-O is strong! He's tough! There's nothing he can't do! Except maybe open really big jars of cookies…

added.title: Go With the Flow
added.description: When Sal stays with Vic & Val, the boys are annoyed by him as their roommate but eventually they learn how cool and magical he is.

added.title: Aluxes
added.description: When Vic finds an ancient relic that summons a gang of mischievous creatures, he uses them to do his bidding, which has disastrous consequences.

added.title: Guillermo's Gathering
added.description: When Vic & Val are forced to go to Guillermo's boring birthday party, they devise a scheme to leave early, but end up discovering that the party is way cooler than they thought.

added.title: Balloon Boys
added.description: Vic & Val go on a hot air balloon trip with Sal and compete to be his favorite, but things go awry when they try to use the magical Nazca Lines to their advantage.

added.title: The Great Bongo Heist
added.description: The boys forget to get Chata a gift for Abuela Day and in a panicked move, they pretend that the bongo drums they borrowed from Xochi are for her. Knowing they have to return the drums, Victor & Valentino pretend to be burglars to steal the bongos back.

added.title: Escape From Bebe Bay
added.description: When Vic & Val accidentally turn themselves and Don into babies, they must escape a daycare center in order to change back to their normal ages.

added.title: Band For Life
added.description: When Vic and Val tag along with Xochi to a punk concert, they want to prove that they're cool enough to hang out with her. But in a desperate attempt to be cool, they wind up destroying the concert.

added.title: Tez Says
added.description: Vic & Val are in awe of the new magician in town, but things go awry when they agree to help him out with a new trick - despite Chata's wishes.

added.title: Forever Ever
added.description: When Vic and Val do a sloppy job cleaning up in Maria Theresa's attic, they accidentally set off a time loop, trapping them in an endless series of chores forever! They must figure out how to stop the loop and return time back to normal.

added.title: Dance Reynaldo Dance
added.description: Vic is desperate to win the cash prize for the dance contest in Monte Macabre and is frustrated that his partner Val won't let him call all the shots. Instead he chooses a different partner: Reynaldo. But Vic pushes Reynaldo too hard to execute his artistic vision. Eventually he learns that in order to be a success, you have to be equal partners.

added.title: There Are No Hoppy Endings
added.description: Chef struggles to maintain his sanity when the kids continue to blame a stuffed rabbit named Hoppy for everything they do wrong.

added.title: Too Much of a Goo'd Thing
added.description: Beth refuses to believe that the adorable goo creature she's created out of slime is consuming the kids until she and Gwen are the only two left in class.

added.title: The Price of Advice
added.description: After a paper origami fortune teller tells Izzy she's the world's best advice giver, she's determined to prove it.

added.title: Mother of All Cards
added.description: Chef attempts to trick the kids into making his mother gifts after he forgets Mother's Day.

added.title: Duncan Disorderly
added.description: Duncan escapes during a community walk only to discover he has to babysit Cody and Bridgette.

added.title: Soother or Later
added.description: A terrified Duncan, who's afraid of lightning, learns it's even harder to break back into school than it was to break out when he finally escapes and finds himself in a dark alley with Izzy during a thunderstorm.

added.title: Camping is In Tents
added.description: A class camping trip turns into a treasure hunt while Harold is determined to catch Bigfoot and keep everyone safe.

added.title: Mutt Ado About Owen
added.description: After accidentally hypnotizing Owen into being a dog, Harold thinks he must reverse the hypnosis to avoid going to jail.

added.title: Simons Are Forever
added.description: Duncan and Leshawna try to take advantage of Izzy's love for the game of Simon Says.

added.title: Stop! Hamster Time
added.description: Owen takes over the job of caring for the class hamster and learns that he's evil.

added.title: Chicken in Chichen Itza Part 1: Pyramid Scheme
added.description: Team Tennyson visits the monuments of Chichen Itza, but when Ben learns about the possible existence of a mythical creature, the Quetzalcoatl, the hero takes it upon himself to find the feathered serpent himself.

added.title: Chicken in Chichen Itza Part 2: The Wages of Fear
added.description: Team Tennyson help transport a caged Quetzalcoatl through the Yucatan jungle, only to encounter a saboteur, La Grange, who hijacks the precious cargo and leads our heroes on a high-octane off-road chase!

added.title: Ben in Rome Part 1: A Slice of Life
added.description: Team Tennyson's quest for the best pizza in Rome leads them to the Bugg Brothers and their latest culinary caper, complete with stolen recipes, kidnapped chefs, shrunken landmarks, and a high-speed chase around the Eternal City.

added.title: Ben in Rome Part 2: The Bee's Knees
added.description: On vacation in Rome, Gwen takes Team Tennyson on a self-guided tour of the many ancient sites, but when a distracted Ben accidentally stumbles upon Queen Bee's monumental heist, the hero must work together with his family if he is to save the city from being sacked for the first time in centuries!

added.title: Funhouse
added.description: The Tennysons find themselves stuck inside an inescapable funhouse constructed by Zombozo; Ben goes alien and fights for escape, ultimately proving that behind every illusion, there's a disappointing secret.

added.title: Summer Breakers
added.description: After Grandpa Max's super smart buddy Phil discovers that a second extraterrestrial item crashed alongside the Omnitrix, Team Tennyson sets off to find the second crash site before someone else does but arrive instead to find nefarious newcomer Breaker One-Nine has already beat them to the punch.

added.title: The Monsters in Your Head
added.description: Ben and Gwen learn a rumor of an alien invasion happening at the park they are camping at, but when they investigate, they discover a preserve containing a host of mutated creatures engineered by Animo! With the unexpected help of Kevin 11 and his family, Ben proves that the rumors are false, and that truth is stranger than fiction!

added.title: Breakup
added.description:
Feeling left out, Adorabat wishes Mao Mao and Badgerclops would spend less time with each other and more time with her. When she gets
what she wishes for and accidentally breaks up their friendship, only the secret of their past can bring them back together.

added.title: Not Impressed
added.description: When a Sweetypie isn't impressed with the sheriff dept's antics, our three heroes try everything to win him over.

added.title: Enemy Mime
added.description: When the Sheriff's Dept fights a monster that copies their every move, they'll have to find a way to fight without fighting.

added.title: Outfoxed
added.description: When Rufus and Reg come to swindle the town, Sheriff Mao Mao teaches them a lesson in justice.

added.title: Bao Bao's Revenge
added.description: When Mao Mao's old partner threatens the kingdom, his friends will need to learn about his past in order to protect the present.

added.title: Popularity Conquest
added.description: When Mao Mao discovers that he is not as popular as Badgerclops and Adorabat, they decide to reinvent him as a kinder, cuddlier hero.

added.title: Sick Mao
added.description: When Mao Mao won't admit that he's sick, he puts the town in danger.

added.title: Thumb War
added.description: The gang decide to compete in the annual Thumb War competition, but a surprise forces Mao Mao to deal with the unthinkable... losing.

added.title: All By Mao Self
added.description: Mao Mao's desire to be a legend drives him to keep topping himself. But how much is enough?

added.title: He's the Sheriff
added.description: The gang struggles to get rid of the King when he joins them as their new deputy-for-a-day!

added.title: The Kid From 3030
added.description: The kids meet a mysterious kid from the future and try to help him complete his mission.

added.title: Power Punchers
added.description: Fed up with losing in video games to his Dad, Craig seeks training in the Creek.

added.title: Creek Cart Racers
added.description: A high-speed race with a high-stakes prize may be too much for Craig and his friends.

added.title: Secret Book Club
added.description: Kelsey starts a super secret book club to introduce Craig and JP to the joys of reading.

added.title: Jextra Perrestrial
added.description: JP believes he may be from another planet, so Craig tries to help him make contact.

added.title: The Takeout Mission
added.description: Kelsey leads her friends on the most important quest ever, picking up takeout for dinner.

added.title: Dinner at the Creek
added.description: Bernard is left in charge for the evening, so Craig sets out to find his own dinner at the creek.

added.title: Jessica's Trail
added.description: Jessica wanders into an unfamiliar creek, leaving Craig to find her before his Mom notices!

added.title: Bug City
added.description: Craig discovers a bunch of bugs under a rock and decides to build them a city.

added.title: Deep Creek Salvage
added.description: The Trio finds gold in the muddy depths of the Creek so Craig builds a rig to recover it.

added.title: Porcupunk Rock
added.description: Madcap turns to Axel and his team for help after a sonic upgrade to Porcupunk threatens to bring down the house.

added.title: Sigue la corriente
added.description: Cuando Sal se queda en lo de Vic y Val, los chicos no lo soportan como compañero, pero finalmente descubren lo genial y mágico que es.

added.title: Aluxes
added.description: Vic encuentra una antigua reliquia que invoca a una pandilla de traviesas criaturas, iy las consecuencias son desastrosas!

added.title: La Fiesta de Guillermo
added.description: Cuando Vic y Val se ven forzados a ir a la aburrida fiesta de cumpleaños de Guillermo, crean un plan para irse temprano, pero terminan descubriendo que la fiesta es mucho mejor de lo que pensaban.

added.title: Ninos de Globo
added.description: Vic y Val salen de viaje en globo aerostático con Sal y compiten por ser su favorito, pero las cosas se complican cuando tratan de usar las mágicas líneas de Nazca a su favor.

added.title: El Gran Robo de Bongos
added.description: Los chicos olvidan conseguir un regalo para Chata en el Día de la Abuela y en un movimiento desesperado, le regalan los bongos que pidieron prestados a Xochi. Sabiendo que deben devolver los tambores, Victor y Valentino fingen ser ladrones para robar los instrumentos.

added.title: Escape de Bahia Bebe
added.description: Cuando, por accidente, Vic y Val se convierten a sí mismos y a Don en bebés, deben escapar de una guardería para poder volver a sus edades normales.

added.title: Banda de por Vida
added.description: Cuando Vic y Val acompañan a Xochi a un concierto punk, quieren demostrar que son lo suficientemente geniales para salir con ella. Pero en un intento desesperado por tener onda, terminan arruinando el concierto.

added.title: Tez dice
added.description: Vic y Val están impresionados con el nuevo mago de la ciudad, pero las cosas se complican cuando aceptan ayudarlo con un nuevo truco, a pesar de los deseos de Chata.

added.title: Eternamente
added.description: Cuando Vic y Val limpian el ático de María Teresa a medias, ipor accidente inician un bucle de tiempo que los atrapa en una serie interminable de tareas eternas! Ahora deben averiguar cómo detener el bucle y devolver el tiempo a la normalidad.

added.title: El Club de Los Solitarios 2, La Isla de las Munecas
added.description: Para probar su valentía, Victor y Valentino se dirigen a una isla embrujada para recuperar una muñeca especial, pero Charlene y Piña están decididos a obtenerla antes que ellos.

added.title: Red Action to the Future
added.description: When Red Action is called to the future for an epic battle, Enid is unsure of what to do.

added.title: Sibling Rivalry
added.description: When a new robot, Raymond, defeats the three heroes to steal the sign to Gar's, KO teams up with Darrell and Shannon to get it back.

added.title: I Am Dendy
added.description: KO helps a strange girl from school, Dendy, get the parts she needs to repair her high tech backpack.

added.title: My Dad Can Beat up Your Dad
added.description: When a bully says his dad can beat up KO's mom, KO gladly accepts the challenge on Carol's behalf.

added.title: You Get Me
added.description: Enid gets turned to stone, and it's up to KO to turn her back to normal.

added.title: Space Invasion
added.description: A visit from Puddle the alien tests the limit of Oscar's hosting skills.

added.title: Momsoon
added.description: Hedgehog gets a call during her radio show from someone who needs her help.

added.title: Sneeze Guard
added.description: Oscar and Hedgehog must work with the witches to cure Alice's camp-threatening illness.

added.title: Susie's Fantastical Scavenger Hunt
added.description: Oscar and Hedgehog must learn to exist without each other when they are put on different teams during a scavenger hunt.

added.title: Mop Forever
added.description: At Alice's dress-up party the campers are magically turned into their costumes.

added.title: Pajamas Party
added.description: When Pajamas starts to panic that Oscar will outgrow her, Oscar tries to help but things go awry.

added.title: The Soundhouse
added.description: Oscar and Hedgehog discover a new structure on the island and become friends with its caretaker.

added.title: Puff Paint
added.description: Oscar's painting is unpopular so he goes on a journey of self-discovery.

added.title: Susie Appreciation Day
added.description: Hedgehog and Oscar find themselves trapped in Susie's cabin and must escape undetected.

added.title: Campers Above the Bed
added.description: Hedgehog finds a city underneath her bed as she looks for her missing diary.

added.title: Daddy-Daughter Card Wars
added.description: To put his embarrassing past behind him, Jake needs his daughter Charlie's help to win an underground Card Wars tourney.

added.title: Eileen Flat Screen
added.description: Rigby wants to set up Eileen's flat screen TV for her.

added.title: Dumped at the Altar
added.description: The guys have to get Muscle Man married.

added.title: Dark Purple
added.description: Susan Strong and her allies infiltrate the mysterious Super Porp factory.

added.title: Trash Cat
added.description: Uncle Grandpa helps a cat who's afraid to take baths.

added.title: Davey
added.description: Finn can't go anywhere without folks stopping to thank him for being a hero.

added.title: Transitional Phase
added.description: Life in the RV is interrupted when Uncle Grandpa and the gang keep mysteriously being sent back and forth through time.

added.title: El Bergerac
added.description: Los Titanes aconsejan a Robin para guiarlo a través de su romance de campamento con Chica Maravilla.

added.title: Do or Diaper
added.description: Mordecai has to kiss Margaret by the end of the week or else wear a diaper.

added.title: The Phone Call
added.description: A threatening phone call from a stranger causes the gang to panic.

added.title: Mojo the Great
added.description: In an effort to make himself great, Mojo steals the powers that makes the each of the Powerpuff girls the heroes they are.

added.title: Largo
added.description: When a mysterious rain cloud plagues Townsville, Bubbles learns things aren't what they seem.

added.title: In the Doghouse
added.description: Buttercup must go it alone to save her family from a kidnapping.

added.title: The Lepre Con
added.description: On a St. Patrick's Day trip to Ireland, Uncle Grandpa and the gang cross paths with a sneaky leprechaun.

added.title: Dad's Dungeon
added.description: Jake's Dad appears in a holographic message with a mysterious challenge for Finn & Jake.

added.title: Man Up 4: The Donnyest Game
added.description: With Man-Boy on the loose, Donny must be prepared for anything.

added.title: The Galactic Enforcers
added.description: Ben joins a trio of intergalactic alien heroes tracking down the bounty hunter Six Six. But this bunch of heroes is not all it's cracked up to be.

added.title: The Package
added.description: The gang gets nutty after repeatedly failing to open a mysterious package.

added.title: Ultimate Weapon
added.description: When Max finds out that part of an alien weapon has been unearthed in Texas, he becomes obsessed with finding it. In doing so, he leads Ben and Gwen on a wild adventure.

added.title: They Lurk Below
added.description: Max's old friend has built the world's only underwater resort, and Ben, Gwen and Max are invited for a sneak peak. But it turns out in order to power the resort, Max's friend took an energy orb from a race of underwater aliens. Now, the aliens want their energy orb back and destroy the resort in order to get it.

added.title: Stump Brothers
added.description: After Clarence and Sumo cause a power outage in Sumo's family home, they're sent off in the hot desert with Sumo's older brother to retrieve a generator part. Will they survive the trek or will Sumo's sibling rivalry boil over?

added.title: Death in Bloom
added.description: Finn and Jake are terrible house sitters and have to go on a quest to replace Princess Bubblegum's rare flower.

added.title: Do Me a Solid
added.description: Mordecai owes Rigby big time when he agrees to go on a double date with him.

added.title: Don
added.description: Rigby's estranged accountant brother comes back to help save the park from an audit. While everyone loves Don, Rigby wants nothing to do with him.

added.title: Viral Spiral
added.description: When the Amoeba Boys wreak havoc on the internet, Bubbles has to hack her sisters in to stop them.

added.title: Mision para llevar
added.description: Kelsey guía a sus amigos en la misión más importante de la historia: buscar la comida para la cena.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Turtle Hats
added.description: While reading a confusing text message in class, Ms. Baker accidentally assigns a weekend project on turtle hats, and the kids struggle to figure out exactly what that entails. When presentation time comes, Clarence, Jeff and Sumo are left to improvise their project on the fly!

added.title: Cena en el Arroyo
added.description: Bernard queda a cargo de sus hermanos durante la noche, así que Craig se va a buscar su propia cena en el Arroyo.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Buscando a Jessica
added.description: Jessica se adentra en un Arroyo desconocido, iy Craig debe encontrarla antes de que su madre se dé cuenta!
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Goldfish Follies
added.description: Clarence buys a goldfish, but when the goldfish bag breaks before he can get home, Clarence must keep his new friend out of harms way and get him back into water before it's too late.

added.title: Ciudad de bichos
added.description: Craig descubre un montón de insectos bajo una roca y decide construirles una ciudad.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Rescate en el Arroyo Profundo
added.description: El trío encuentra oro en las fangosas profundidades del Arroyo, por lo que Craig construye un equipo para recuperarlo.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Straight Illin
added.description: In an escalating series of dares, Clarence eats five hundred hard-boiled eggs, delighting the kids around him. As Clarence grows sicker and sicker, the kids get more and more grossed out until they want nothing to do with him.

added.title: Hurricane Dilliss
added.description: Things in the Wendle household are turned upside down when Mary's mom Dyllis comes to visit, butting her way into every corner of Clarence, Mary and Chad's life.

added.title: Something Zombozo This Way Comes
added.description: Ben and Rook must stop Zombozo and the Circus Freaks from turning everyone in Bellwood into zombie clowns!

added.title: Enemy of My Enemy
added.description: When a grudge match between Fire Man and Namagem threatens to level Silicon City, Mega Man must intervene and ultimately choose a side to prevent collateral damage.

added.title: Bengeance is Mine
added.description: Vilgax' former lackey Psyphon is elated when his master returns.

added.title: Old School
added.description: Mega Man must stop Chaotique from making Silicon Central disappear, as in literally erasing the school at a subatomic level, while learning life lessons from a rambling old-bot named Hal.

added.title: This Is Not a Drill
added.description: Mega Man and Dr. Light must set aside a father-son disagreement to stop Drill Man from taking revenge on his own overbearing father.

added.title: Animo Crackers
added.description: Dr. Animo from the future comes back to the present to help himself defeat Ben once and for all. (Introducing new Ben alien, Gutrot.)

added.title: A Man Man for All Seasons
added.description: When a run-in with the Hoover Gang leaves Aki unable to transform into Mega Man, he must don a cheap costume and enlist the unlikeliest of sidekicks, Man Man!

added.title: Change the Charge
added.description: Mega Man tries to stop Elec Man by helping him overcome his destructive habits, but is he being duped in the process?

added.title: Charmed, I'm Sure
added.description: Still stranded on the monster planet Anur Transyl, Ben and Rook reluctantly team up with Charmcaster to take on Zs' Skayr.

added.title: Catfight
added.description: The princesses Looma and Attea are at odds over who gets to marry Ben!

added.title: Enfermo
added.description: Cuando Mao Mao no quiere reconocer que está enfermo, pone al pueblo en peligro.

added.title: Bobo Chan
added.description: Colosal adopta a un monstruo abandonado, pero es mejor dejar algunas cosas en estado salvaje.

added.title: El es el Sheriff
added.description: iEl trío lucha por deshacerse del Rey cuando los acompaña como nuevo ayudante del sheriff por un día!

added.title: La Aventura Perfecta
added.description: Cuando a Mao Mao se le antoja vivir la aventura perfecta, Adorabat dice una mentira piadosa.

added.title: Lucha de Pulgares
added.description: El trío decide concursar en la competencia anual de Lucha de Pulgares, pero una sorpresa obliga a Mao Mao a lidiar con algo impensado… la derrota.

added.title: Blast Resort
added.description: Mega Man must assist Blasto Woman in a heist to stop a powerful EMP emitter from falling into the wrong hands.

added.title: Too Much Is Never Enough
added.description: Envious of Namagem's ability to wield more than three powers at a time, Mega Man tries taking all of his replicated schematics on board, with grave side effects.

added.title: The Bluster Bunch
added.description: A trail of tornadic destruction leads Mega Man, Suna, and Rush through a series of encounters with Air Man's quirky siblings.

added.title: It's Chemistry, Man
added.description: Chemistry Man lays siege to Silicon Central when he discovers that his replacement, Miss CHO, has been presented with a teaching award.

added.title: Flower Power
added.description: Mega Man must battle Wood Man for the fate of the Corpse Flower, a rare and noxious bloom that's stinking up all of Silicon City.

added.title: El chico del 3030
added.description: Los niños conocen a un misterioso niño del futuro y tratan de ayudarlo a completar su misión.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Punos Fuertes
added.description: Harto de perder cuando juega a los videojuegos contra su padre, Craig busca entrenarse en el Arroyo.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Carrera en el Arroyo
added.description: Una carrera de alta velocidad con un premio de alto riesgo puede ser demasiado para Craig y sus amigos.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Club de Lectura Secreto
added.description: Kelsey crea un club de lectura supersecreto para introducir a Craig y JP en las alegrías de la lectura.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Jextra Perrestre
added.description: JP cree que puede ser de otro planeta, así que Craig trata de ayudarlo a hacer contacto.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: La Venganza de Bao Bao
added.description: Cuando el antiguo compañero de Mao Mao amenaza al reino, los amigos de Mao Mao tendrán que conocer su pasado para proteger el presente.

added.title: No Me Impresiona
added.description: Cuando un Corazoncito no se siente impresionado con las hazañas del departamento del sheriff, nuestros tres héroes intentan de todo para conquistarlo.

added.title: Enemigo Mimo
added.description: Cuando el departamento del sheriff se enfrenta a un monstruo que copia todos los movimientos, tendrán que encontrar el modo de pelear sin pelear.

added.title: Todo Por Mao Mismo
added.description: El deseo de Mao Mao de convertirse en leyenda lo lleva a querer superarse a sí mismo una y otra vez. ¿Pero cuánto es suficiente?

added.title: Superado
added.description: Cuando Rufus y Reg llegan para engañar al pueblo, el sheriff Mao Mao les enseña una lección sobre la justicia.

removed.title: Clayton
removed.description: Darwin needs to find a photo of Clayton to put on the cover of the school yearbook - but he makes the mistake of seeking help from Tobias, who has his eye on the cover spot himself! Featuring hilarious clips from the first six seasons of 'The Amazing World of Gumball'.

removed.title: Xingo Nation
removed.description: Kevin 11 gives Xingo a power up - setting him loose to wreak havoc on other TV shows - and it is up to Ben to stop them both.

removed.title: And Xingo Was His Name-O
removed.description: When a new Xingo app mysteriously appears on Gwen's tablet, Ben can't help himself and activates it despite his cousin's disapproval, springing a trap that transports Ben in the animated world and Xingo back in the real world. It's the ol' switcheroo!

removed.title: Follow Your Dreams
removed.description: Apple and Onion need to find a dream to follow, so that their lives don't head nowhere.

removed.title: Positive Attitude Theory
removed.description: Apple and Onion spend a day in Falafel's shoes and use their positive attitude to prove he shouldn't be so grumpy.

removed.title: Banana Joe
removed.description: When Principal Brown sets Darwin the task of making the school yearbook, Darwin starts by asking class clown Banana Joe for a simple selfie to put on the cover. But with Banana Joe, things are never that simple. Featuring hilarious clips from the first six seasons of 'The Amazing World of Gumball'.

removed.title: The Night Ben Tennyson Came to Town
removed.description: Team Tennyson travels to Wheeler, "the liveliest mining town on Route 66", but when Ben becomes paranoid that the Forever Knight is out to get him, he must try to convince his fam while also stopping his new foe from destroying the town.

removed.title: Not Funny
removed.description: With their 6 month friend anniversary approaching, Apple has to find a way not to lose his best friend.

removed.title: Apple's Short
removed.description: Apple needs to be tall so that he can be in love.

removed.title: Face Your Fears
removed.description: Apple and Onion must face their fears while trapped in a pet shop, so they can save French Fry from facing hers.

removed.title: Heads of the Family
removed.description: Team Tennyson stops in at a fringe family reunion, and Ben encounters a whole lot more than kooky cousins— namely, Kevin 11 and the Bugg Brothers, whose latest crackpot invention sparks a series of hilarious head-swaps between all parties.

removed.title: Fear in the Family
removed.description: Ben and Gwen can't wait for the Omni-Copter to arrive at the Great Pyramids, but when bad weather disrupts their flight, they soon come face-to-face with The Fogg and its spawn: The Fogg Family!

removed.title: Heat of the Moment
removed.description: After Ben easily dispatches the Weatherheads, Team Tennyson travels to a ski resort for some fun in the snow but when Ben runs into the Weatherheads yet again, this time they are a force to reckon with, now that Kevin 11 has used his Bootleg powers to unlock their emotional controls!

removed.title: My Bodyguard
removed.description: When Zombozo hypnotizes Grandpa Max's entire baking class it is up to Ben and Gwen to clean up the mess, but it gets even messier when Zombozo unveils his new bodyguard: Kevin 11!

removed.title: Wheels of Fortune
